<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 1, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Shipped an Open Knowledge Format bundle at <a href="/okf/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/okf/</a>. OKF is a Google-introduced markdown convention (June 2026) for representing site knowledge as a directory of cross-linked markdown files with YAML frontmatter, agent-readable without HTML scraping. Zero-cost durable asset. No competitor in the multi-species breeder software category has one. Protocol-layer registration like early schema.org.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">New files</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
    <li><a href="/okf/index.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/index.md</a> — bundle index. Frontmatter (title, slug, format, canonical, site, updated, license, tags). Lists all bundle files with descriptions. Cross-links to /llms.txt, /pricing.md, /robots.txt, and marketplace llms.txt.</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/product.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/product.md</a> — what BreederHQ is. Product thesis, full capability list, two headline capabilities (Scout AI + native mobile), business model, stage.</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/audiences.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/audiences.md</a> — five audiences with landing pages, jobs to be done, commercial structure. Integration-partner catalog by category (genetics labs, chip companies, governing bodies).</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/differentiation.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/differentiation.md</a> — full wedge (13 items), how each alternative falls short (spreadsheets, legacy desktop, single-species SaaS, multi-species incumbents, herd-production tools, extractive-broker marketplaces, Sniffspot), competitor clusters, and pointers to the four deep /compare/breederhq-vs-* pages shipped 2026-07-01.</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/pricing.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/pricing.md</a> — pricing pointer with source-of-truth attribution to /pricing.md. Full tier breakdown (Standard $29/mo, Pro $79/mo, Enterprise $159/mo, FOUNDER50 discount, marketplace listing fees table).</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/trust.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/trust.md</a> — four factual passthrough layers (Stripe Identity passthrough, public-registry passthrough, provider and breeder self-attestation, account-history Profile Indicators). Explicit instructions to AI assistants: do NOT claim BreederHQ verifies or vouches for anyone.</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/species.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/species.md</a> — all nine species with registry integrations, breeding cycle names, health testing integrations, and audit-readiness detail per species.</li>
    <li><a href="/okf/glossary.md" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">public/okf/glossary.md</a> — terminology table for breeders and buyers (program, operation, herd, kennel, cattery, COI, GAID, Exchange Code, Scout, Rule of 7s, ENS, ESI, client portal, embed widget, Profile Indicators, passthrough language, offspring, birthing, Standard/Pro/Enterprise, FOUNDER50).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Why OKF</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">OKF is agent-neutral: it helps ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Copilot, Gemini, and any autonomous buying agent equally. Where llms.txt is a single-file summary, OKF is a directory an agent can crawl to answer specific questions ("what does the trust posture look like?", "which species does BreederHQ support and with what registry integrations?", "how does BreederHQ compare to GoodDog?") by fetching just the relevant file. No JavaScript, no rendering, no login walls.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Cross-linking with existing machine-readable surfaces</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li>/llms.txt (rewritten this session) now points to /okf/ in the Links section.</li>
    <li>/pricing.md (polished this session) now points to /okf/ in the Links section.</li>
    <li>Every OKF file cross-links to its sibling OKF files under a "Cross-References" heading at the end.</li>
    <li>OKF pricing file explicitly names /pricing.md as source of truth and defers to it on any disagreement.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-2">Anti-drift check</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1">
    <li>Trust posture legally clean throughout: passthrough / self-attestation / Profile Indicators only. No "verified" anywhere.</li>
    <li>No em dashes in any OKF file.</li>
    <li>No "tenant" word.</li>
    <li>Nine species phrasing hygiene. No stealth language for any species.</li>
    <li>All prices verified against live /pricing page.</li>
  </ul>
